 Kubernetes ResourceQuota — Control Your Cluster Resources
In Kubernetes, multiple teams share the same cluster. Without limits, one team can consume all resources.
👉 ResourceQuota helps solve this problem.
📌 What is ResourceQuota?
It is used to limit the total amount of resources that can be used within a namespace.
📌 What can we limit?
CPU usage
Memory usage
Number of Pods
Services and ConfigMaps
📌 Why is it important?
Prevents resource overuse
Ensures fair usage across teams
Avoids cluster performance issues
📌 Example:
Limit a namespace to:
4 CPUs
8GB Memory
10 Pods
If the limit is exceeded, Kubernetes will reject new resource creation.
💡 Best Practice:
Always define ResourceQuota for production namespaces to maintain stability.
📊 Simple Rule:
Namespace → Limited Resources → Controlled Usage
